				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				As an Erudite, I felt left out of the previous cultural armors. No More! I'm proud to share <BR>
the news that Erudite Tailoring is active! Woot!<BR>
<BR>
On an existing vendor in Erudin, in the open area opposite the fountain from the Erud's Forge and armor shop, is sold three metal threads, an Erudite Sewing Kit, and a scroll entitled On Terrorantula Silk. The contents of the scroll follow:<BR>
<BR>
I recently had the fortune to purchase a strange silk from a traveller hailing from the Deserts of Ro. After experimenting for quite some time with the new material I discovered that when sewn into swatches it could be cured with Purified Mana, threaded with Platinum Thread, and using an appropriate pattern tailored into an armor as strong as steel!!<BR>
<BR>
The scroll reads on in typical fashion stating how many swatches are used in each piece:<BR>
1 swatch - helm, collar, mask, pauldron, bracer<BR>
2 swatches - waistband, vambraces, gauntlets, boots<BR>
3 swatches - breastplate, cloak, greaves<BR>
<BR>
The Terrorantula is a rare spawn in South Ro, a HUGE spider. I have seen it once before. The Purify Mana is an enchanter spell, similar to the Velious tailoring recipes' use of other types of mana.<BR>
<BR>
I am so excited to bring this to your attention! As a master of all trade skills, I have been looking forward to this since it was promised by VI many months ago. Good luck in your crafts, let's get working to make some and get stats and even trivials up on this board!<BR>
<BR>
-=\=- Solecism -=\=-<BR>
Craftkeeper of the 32nd Order, Brell Sirilis server<BR>
Master of All Trade Skills<BR>
and finally, Erudite Cultural Armorer
				</font>
